  "response": "Carnotaurus, like many other theropod dinosaurs, is believed to have had slitted pupils, similar to those found in some modern reptiles. This feature would have potentially allowed for better vision and adaptability in varying light conditions, similar to the ways slitted pupils function in animals today. However, direct evidence such as preserved eye structures is not available for Carnotaurus, so this remains an educated hypothesis based on comparisons with related species and their ecological niches.",
